The paper deals with the weight distributions of cyclic codes, which is a topic in coding theory and information theory (cs.IT). It also mentions the practical importance of cyclic codes in cryptography, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on a class of optimal three-weight cyclic codes, which is a subfield of cyclic codes (cs.CC). The paper also mentions the algebraic structure of cyclic codes, which is a topic in discrete mathematics and algebraic geometry (cs.DS). Lastly, the paper discusses the capabilities of error detection and correction for linear codes, which is a topic in signal processing and information theory (cs.SI).
